  "culturalTip": "Korean coffee shops use Italian words for the names of coffee items, such as 카페 라떼 [ka-pe la-tte] (caffé latte) or 카푸치노 [ka-pu-chi-no] (cappuccino). For other items besides coffee, loanwords are usually used, which are just English words written in Hangul and pronounced with a Korean accent. Some common menu items that are loanwords include 오렌지 주스 [o-ren-ji ju-seul] (orange juice) and 캐모마일 티 [kae-mo-ma-il ti] (chamomile tea).",
